    "recap_headline": "University of Richmond Athletics",
    "recap_text": "RICHMOND, Va. \u2013\nThe Richmond baseball team got back in the win column Tuesday with a 7-5 victory over the Maryland Terrapins at Pitt Field to close out a 12-game home stand.\nRichmond, now 11-10 on the year and 0-3 in Atlantic 10 action, heads on the road this weekend to face Fordham in the Bronx, NY in conference play starting on Friday. All three games will be streamed on ESPN+.\nAfter Maryland took a 1-0 lead in the first inning off two hits and two walks, UR starter\nKhristopher Morris\ngot out of the inning with a strikeout. Morris worked a scoreless second inning, allowing one hit and a hit batter but stranded both Terps.\nRichmond got on the board in the second inning when\nAidan O'Keefe\nput down a safety squeeze bunt to score\nSean Scanlon\nand\nChris Schaller\n.\nJackson Kraemer\nthen hit his first home run of the season to deep left field to give Richmond a 3-1 lead.\nSam Young\ntossed a scoreless third inning, walking one, hitting one and striking out two.\nChristian Dray\nchipped in two scoreless innings, but the Terps tagged him for four runs in the sixth inning. Dray finished with a pitching line of two innings and a third, allowing four runs on three hits, a walk, a hit batter and three strikeouts.\nDylan Siesky\ngot the final two outs of the sixth, including one out via a strikeout.\nThe Spiders answered with four runs in the bottom of the sixth, all with two outs.\nDylan Winebrenner\ndoubled down the left field line bringing in two runs to tie the game.\nMichael Elko\nbrought in two more runs with a sharp base hit to center field to give the Spiders a 7-5 lead.\nKeane Hyer\ngot the one batter he faced out in the seventh before\nBijan Anvar\nfinished retiring the side including a strikeout.\nAaron Van Tuyle\ntossed a scoreless eighth, also retiring the side in order and picked up a strikeout.\nKellan Heney\nretired the one batter he faced to start the ninth.\nJustin Gay\ncollected the save after working around a base hit with a fly out and a ground out to finish the game."
